WEBVTT

00:02.330 --> 00:05.367
Violet:
Come on, pick up,
pick up, pick up.

00:05.400 --> 00:07.288
Nova, you should be driving
to St. Jo's right now.

00:07.340 --> 00:09.308
You know how these storms
shift every which way.

00:09.340 --> 00:13.504
So, whatever you're doing,
stop and get your behind here.

00:13.540 --> 00:15.633
Okay?

00:15.680 --> 00:17.477
All right.

00:19.150 --> 00:21.243
Newscaster over TV:
The National Hurricane Center

00:21.280 --> 00:22.747
has issued a tropical
storm warning

00:22.790 --> 00:25.213
for southern Louisiana
and coastal MISSISSIppI.

00:25.250 --> 00:28.481
And a direct strike
of Tropical Storm Peter
is expected.

00:28.520 --> 00:30.181
Well, this sucks.

00:30.230 --> 00:31.583
Last week's interview
sealed the deal.

00:31.630 --> 00:33.621
Today was just
a meet and greet.

00:33.660 --> 00:35.525
Relax, honey.

00:35.560 --> 00:38.290
Y'all ain't still planning
to go to that school?

00:38.330 --> 00:40.389
Doubt it.
Not in this weather.

00:40.440 --> 00:41.759
When are we going
to reschedule the tour then?

00:41.800 --> 00:44.530
A tour of what?
That place ain't college.

00:44.570 --> 00:48.677
Gardini Prep is NOLA's
top private school, Aunt Vi.

00:48.710 --> 00:52.111
Did y'all think about going
to St. Jo's high school?

00:52.150 --> 00:54.641
Newscaster:
Now, as you know, our last
big storm on record...

00:54.680 --> 00:55.817
( scoffs )

00:55.850 --> 00:59.217
Well, schools don't turn
their nose up at St. Jo's.

00:59.260 --> 01:03.151
LSU, Ole Miss...

01:03.190 --> 01:05.124
Texas Tech.

01:05.160 --> 01:06.559
And the list goes on.

01:06.600 --> 01:08.591
I think Micah's looking
more to, you know,

01:08.630 --> 01:11.098
Harvard, Stanford, MIT.

01:11.130 --> 01:12.631
The other Ivies.

01:14.200 --> 01:15.462
Yeah.

01:15.500 --> 01:17.764
They're closed
due to inclement weather.

01:17.810 --> 01:21.302
Well, good.
Micah, you can go take
them fancy clothes off

01:21.340 --> 01:22.841
and grab all the blankets,

01:22.880 --> 01:25.371
coats and towels
out that closet.

01:25.410 --> 01:26.809
Is it going to get
that bad?

01:26.850 --> 01:28.477
Well, we're going to
treat it like a snow day.

01:28.520 --> 01:30.283
Make some fun out of it.

01:30.320 --> 01:32.311
I got to go.

01:32.360 --> 01:34.487
- Wait, you're leaving?
- Where are you going?

01:34.520 --> 01:36.283
I got to go check
on the farm.

01:36.330 --> 01:38.651
You tell Ralph Angel
I said to bring that boy
over here.

01:38.690 --> 01:41.124
Everybody knows this is
the family safe house.

01:41.160 --> 01:42.388
Hollywood's there.

01:42.430 --> 01:44.489
What do I tell him?

01:45.770 --> 01:48.295
Iwmmmy
He's grown.

01:48.340 --> 01:49.762
He can take care
of himself.

01:49.810 --> 01:52.677
And whoever else he's got
over there taking care of.

01:54.410 --> 01:55.877
Newscaster over TV:
Take this seriously.

01:55.910 --> 01:58.299
This is a major event.
This is Tropical Storm Peter...

01:58.350 --> 02:01.171
( music plays )

02:01.220 --> 02:02.619
* Dreams never die

02:02.650 --> 02:04.641
* Take flight
as the world turns *

02:04.690 --> 02:06.385
* Dreams never die

02:06.420 --> 02:08.752
* Take flight
as the world turns *

02:08.790 --> 02:10.485
* The colors in the lines

02:10.530 --> 02:12.657
* Take flight

02:12.700 --> 02:14.793
* Dreams never die

02:20.400 --> 02:23.733
* Keep the colors
in the lines *

02:23.770 --> 02:27.831
* Keep the colors
in the lines, take flight *

02:27.880 --> 02:29.541
Newscaster over radio:
The heavy rain expected

02:29.580 --> 02:31.798
from Tropical Storm Peter
may potentially

02:31.850 --> 02:33.818
put mild pressure on the levees
here in New Orleans.

02:33.850 --> 02:36.239
Though the rain has yet
to begin to fall,

02:36.290 --> 02:37.541
- expect some light sprinkles--
- Miss Blanche,

02:37.590 --> 02:38.739
don't your niece
need a ride?

02:38.790 --> 02:41.281
Holy Cross will be
on the evac list

02:41.320 --> 02:42.685
if they have to put one out.

02:42.730 --> 02:45.255
_Her boss don't care
If a hurricane coming

02:45.290 --> 02:46.791
or the end of the world.

02:46.830 --> 02:48.821
They already said they're going
to fire that girl

02:48.860 --> 02:51.328
if she don't come in
In the morning.

02:51.370 --> 02:52.928
Newscaster:
There Is_a concern
at this hour

02:52.970 --> 02:54.562
that Tropical Storm Peter
could shift course,

02:54.600 --> 02:55.828
possibly making
landfall tonight,

02:55.870 --> 02:58.964
posing the most acute threat
from a tropical system

02:59.010 --> 03:00.807
since Hurricane Sandy.

03:00.840 --> 03:03.547
All indications have Peter
reaching New Orleans...

03:03.580 --> 03:06.469
The Ninth is not ready
for another hurricane.

03:06.520 --> 03:08.272
It's barely ready
for a sunny day.

03:08.320 --> 03:10.379
( cell phone rings )

03:10.420 --> 03:11.614
Aunt Vi?

03:11.650 --> 03:13.584
I'll call her back.

03:15.460 --> 03:17.758
Your niece will be okay,
Miss Blanche.

03:18.990 --> 03:21.754
The Lord willing
and the creek don't rise.

03:21.800 --> 03:23.688
Newscaster:
...as to the length
and duration of Peter.

03:23.730 --> 03:25.561
We're hoping it stops
during the night,

03:25.600 --> 03:27.636
but very possible
that it continues on

03:27.670 --> 03:29.809
for a day or two after.

03:29.840 --> 03:32.832
( radio static crackles )

03:32.880 --> 03:36.543
How the hell we supposed
to ride out a hurricane here?

03:36.580 --> 03:38.445
You ain't got nothing.

03:38.480 --> 03:40.448
Ain't no hurricane yet.

03:40.480 --> 03:42.710
But we got food.

03:42.750 --> 03:46.311
What, stale-ass cereal
and three-day-old milk?

03:49.630 --> 03:52.724
Flashlights. Batteries.

03:52.760 --> 03:54.523
Look, I got what Pop had,
all right?

03:54.560 --> 03:55.925
That means you ain't
got nothing.

03:55.960 --> 03:58.292
Hell, I see why you was
always at Vi's house.

03:58.330 --> 03:59.695
- Hey.
- Hey!

03:59.740 --> 04:01.469
( Charley gasps )

04:01.500 --> 04:02.637
Ralph Angel:
Hey, what's up, sis?

04:02.670 --> 04:04.035
Look who it is!

04:04.070 --> 04:05.367
Mwah!

04:05.410 --> 04:06.536
- Hi, baby.
- Got to go.

04:06.580 --> 04:08.935
- Okay.
- Okay.

04:08.980 --> 04:11.471
- Prosper still out there?
- No, he headed home.

04:11.510 --> 04:12.716
Remy out there, though.

04:12.750 --> 04:14.911
What about the workers?
Are they still here?

04:14.950 --> 04:18.283
Yeah, but they need to get paid
before they leave.

04:18.320 --> 04:20.413
- You bring cash?
- Yeah.

04:20.460 --> 04:22.621
Is the rest
of the cane in?

04:22.660 --> 04:24.059
Ralph Angel:
Only 10 acres left to go.

04:24.090 --> 04:26.593
Good. They need to finish,
because if it floods--

04:26.630 --> 04:28.598
Oh, it's going to flood.

04:28.630 --> 04:31.019
The only question is,
how much?

04:31.070 --> 04:33.061
Wood, Ralph Angel,

04:33.100 --> 04:34.965
can we pay these guys
so they can take off?

04:35.000 --> 04:36.308
Yeah.

04:36.340 --> 04:38.035
- Hey.
- Hey.

04:39.110 --> 04:41.704
( thunder rumbles )

04:41.740 --> 04:43.503
Charley:
So they're done planting?

04:43.550 --> 04:45.404
No. Prosper said
to let them leave.

04:45.450 --> 04:48.749
No, we need to finish
this now. That's the point
of all of this.

04:48.780 --> 04:50.748
( speaks Spanish )

04:50.790 --> 04:52.758
( speaking Spanish )

04:58.660 --> 05:00.059
( workers murmuring )

05:00.100 --> 05:02.591
Charley, pay them
and let them leave.

05:02.630 --> 05:06.498
Yeah, their bus pickup
way over near Jones' farm.
That's 40 minutes from here.

05:06.540 --> 05:08.792
No, but the weather report
says that it's just
a tropical storm.

05:08.840 --> 05:11.502
The weather changes
quick here. They stay
an hour away.

05:11.540 --> 05:13.770
You want to risk them
mIssmg the bus and being
stuck here?

05:13.810 --> 05:15.675
They can finish the planting
and still make the bus.

05:15.710 --> 05:17.803
( speaks Spanish )

05:18.950 --> 05:22.340
Uh, after--
( speaks Spanish )

05:22.390 --> 05:23.482
Okay?

05:23.520 --> 05:25.442
Gracias.

05:25.490 --> 05:27.310
Charley:
Gracias.

05:30.630 --> 05:32.029
Gracias.

05:32.060 --> 05:32.856
Man:
Vamos.

05:32.900 --> 05:35.721
( all speaking Spanish )

05:39.100 --> 05:40.692
( sighs )

05:51.650 --> 05:53.868
( thunder rumbles )

06:07.960 --> 06:10.099
Newscaster over radio:
Doppler radar IS Indicating

06:10.130 --> 06:12.394
_ that Hurricane Peter
IS coming up With more force

06:12.440 --> 06:13.862
- with the coastal winds...
- A hurricane?

06:13.900 --> 06:14.992
- Damn.
- Only a matter of time

06:15.040 --> 06:17.702
that we were officially
given the upgrade

06:17.740 --> 06:19.469
to a category 1 hurricane,

06:19.510 --> 06:22.604
with winds now reaching
around 70 miles per hour.

06:22.650 --> 06:23.878
Experts expect this...

06:23.910 --> 06:25.969
You want to stay
at my place?

06:27.850 --> 06:29.738
It's a little soon
for that, ain't it?

06:29.790 --> 06:33.453
I meant for safety, Nova.

06:35.160 --> 06:37.185
Sorry about that.
I'm just not a...

06:37.230 --> 06:39.790
"two dates and a U-Haul"
kind of girl.

06:43.230 --> 06:45.721
( cell phone rings )

06:45.770 --> 06:47.135
Calvin.

06:47.170 --> 06:48.797
Don't pick up.

06:50.470 --> 06:51.801
( silences ringer)

06:53.580 --> 06:55.878
You're our last stop,
Miss Blanche.

06:57.680 --> 06:59.819
You a blessing, baby.

07:14.530 --> 07:17.761
That's all you got for me
in that bag of yours?

07:17.800 --> 07:20.496
Newscaster:
...80% of New Orleans_was
submerged at one pomt,

07:20.540 --> 07:23.202
The water reached
six to 12 miles inland...

07:23.240 --> 07:26.061
Now this here, this is what
I'm talking about.

07:26.110 --> 07:28.999
This will get me
through any storm.

07:29.040 --> 07:31.770
- Okay! Yes, indeed.
- ( Miss Blanche laughs )

07:31.810 --> 07:34.540
Nova:
You be safe now.

07:34.580 --> 07:37.185
Watch your step.

07:37.220 --> 07:38.539
There we go.

07:39.720 --> 07:41.256
( door slides closed )

07:41.290 --> 07:43.224
Newscaster:
...very unlikely
that Peter will be

07:43.260 --> 07:46.627
even remotely as destructive
as some of his predecessors,

07:46.660 --> 07:48.821
the danger is real...

07:48.860 --> 07:50.464
( phone line rings )

07:52.540 --> 07:54.838
Violet over phone:
You scared me half to death.

07:54.870 --> 07:56.929
Are you on the 10
headed this way?

07:56.970 --> 07:58.699
No, not yet.
I'll be leaving soon.

07:58.740 --> 08:00.571
Why haven't you left yet?

08:00.610 --> 08:03.044
I had to help out
a few folks in the Ninth.
You know how it is.

08:03.080 --> 08:05.605
I know how it was
last time.

08:05.650 --> 08:07.811
Stop worrying, Aunt Vi.

08:07.850 --> 08:09.613
Well, I'm going to worry,

08:09.650 --> 08:11.242
because you gave me cause to.

08:11.290 --> 08:14.612
You hacking your way
out that roof, up there
nearly a day.

08:14.660 --> 08:16.480
We could have lost you.

08:17.690 --> 08:19.726
But y'all didn't.

08:19.760 --> 08:22.092
I have a responsibility
to my neighbors,

08:22.130 --> 08:24.291
especially when
they can't help themselves.

08:24.330 --> 08:27.993
Yeah, well,
that's all and good,
but now this a hurricane,

08:28.040 --> 08:30.907
so you get yourself
on the 10 before
Pontchartrain flood.

08:30.940 --> 08:33.602
Please. And call me
when you do.

08:33.640 --> 08:35.278
Okay, Aunt Vi. I will.

08:35.310 --> 08:37.801
Newscaster over TV:
Wind gusts up to
95 miles an hour,

08:37.850 --> 08:39.875
which is gonna be
pretty intense...

08:39.920 --> 08:41.979
( sighs )

08:44.690 --> 08:47.011
Don't be scratching up
my truck.

08:47.060 --> 08:49.688
Ain't nobody
scratching nothing up.

08:49.730 --> 08:51.584
What I look like?

09:08.240 --> 09:11.141
* I can't get no loving *

09:11.180 --> 09:12.909
What you doing here,
Darla?

09:12.950 --> 09:14.542
I wanted to give Blue
his birthday gift.

09:18.350 --> 09:22.980
A hurricane coming,
and here you go being you,
huh?

09:23.030 --> 09:25.783
You're too late.
You can't even get
his birthday right.

09:25.830 --> 09:27.650
I didn't have the money
last month.

09:29.700 --> 09:32.066
- Can I give it to him?
- No.

09:32.100 --> 09:35.035
You can't just come in
and see him whenever
you want.

09:35.070 --> 09:37.038
That ain't how this work.

09:37.070 --> 09:38.765
Look, go home, Darla.

09:38.810 --> 09:41.370
You ain't got no business
being out in this weather
no way.

09:41.410 --> 09:42.672
All right?

09:42.710 --> 09:45.941
They evacuated
my trailer park.

09:45.980 --> 09:49.279
I just stopped by
on the way to the shelter.

09:49.320 --> 09:52.084
( sighs )

09:52.120 --> 09:55.886
You ain't got no new friends
at that city hall job of yours?

09:55.920 --> 09:56.955
Blue:
Mommy!

09:56.990 --> 09:58.287
( Darla gasps )

09:58.330 --> 10:00.798
Hi! You got so big!

10:00.830 --> 10:02.297
Mommy!

10:02.330 --> 10:05.299
Darla:
Oh, my goodness,
look at you!

10:05.330 --> 10:07.639
Is that for me?

10:07.670 --> 10:09.365
Who else
would it be for?

10:10.670 --> 10:12.103
- Checkers?
- Mm-hmm.

10:12.140 --> 10:13.676
Blue:
Can we play?

10:13.710 --> 10:15.905
- Just for a little bit, buddy.
- Blue: Okay.

10:15.940 --> 10:17.805
( door opens )

10:17.850 --> 10:18.976
Don't push it.

10:19.010 --> 10:20.739
( gasps )

10:20.780 --> 10:23.044
How about we play
Go Fish first?

10:23.090 --> 10:24.785
Blue:
Ooh, that sounds good.

10:24.820 --> 10:26.708
Ain't no time for games now,
all right?

10:26.760 --> 10:28.978
All the roads around St. Jo's
done closed up.

10:29.020 --> 10:30.749
Hurricane done shifted.

10:30.790 --> 10:32.621
Upgraded to a category 2.

10:47.240 --> 10:47.729
I'm worried about him.

10:50.280 --> 10:52.305
Violet, too.

10:52.350 --> 10:53.977
If two people
want to get together,

10:54.020 --> 10:56.011
can't nothing
hold that back.

10:56.050 --> 10:58.109
Not even themselves.

11:00.890 --> 11:03.222
You don't need to waste time
over here helping us out

11:03.260 --> 11:06.058
when you got a house
of your own to take care of.

11:06.090 --> 11:09.025
Lady, I felt this storm
coming a week ago.

11:09.060 --> 11:11.858
My place is ready
for whatever may come,

11:11.900 --> 11:13.959
hell or high water.

11:14.000 --> 11:15.297
You a psychic?

11:15.340 --> 11:17.433
Just a man with a bum knee.

11:17.470 --> 11:19.802
( both laugh )

11:20.910 --> 11:22.138
Uh-uh-uh.

11:22.180 --> 11:24.307
About to get splinters
all in your hands.

11:24.350 --> 11:25.772
Let it go. Here.

11:44.130 --> 11:45.859
Just put it there.

11:47.200 --> 11:49.907
Aunt Vi's the only place
to hole up, Darla.

11:49.940 --> 11:51.066
Ralph Angel:
Ain't no backup.

11:51.110 --> 11:53.931
Come on.
Come on, boy.

11:53.980 --> 11:56.744
The storm might not
be that bad.

11:56.780 --> 11:58.179
Hop in the truck, Blue.

11:58.210 --> 12:00.246
Violet probably won't
have the room for all of us.

12:00.280 --> 12:02.942
What you gonna do,
Darla?

12:02.990 --> 12:04.844
We ain't got all day.

12:04.890 --> 12:06.118
Come on.

12:09.320 --> 12:11.322
I'll put all of them
back there.

12:14.260 --> 12:15.955
- I got yours.
- Thank you.

12:16.000 --> 12:17.365
You got it.

12:20.270 --> 12:22.033
Y'all finish up
that last window.

12:22.070 --> 12:23.367
I'm going to meet
y'all at Vi's.

12:23.410 --> 12:24.502
Yeah.

12:32.580 --> 12:34.844
( starts engine )

12:34.880 --> 12:36.245
See y'all later.

12:36.280 --> 12:37.986
- Hey, be careful.
- Holleood: You too, now.

12:38.020 --> 12:41.114
I'm going to bring them in,
release them,

12:41.160 --> 12:43.287
and then I'll bring in
the combine from the fields.

12:43.330 --> 12:44.957
( car engine starts )

12:44.990 --> 12:46.924
But they haven't
finished it yet.

12:46.960 --> 12:48.848
You want them
to get stuck out there?

12:50.570 --> 12:52.322
I'll do it.

13:00.440 --> 13:02.533
( newscaster speaking
over TV)

13:02.580 --> 13:05.299
Okay, baby, put that water
in the refrigerator

13:05.350 --> 13:08.012
and crank it on high
so that the food won't spoil

13:08.050 --> 13:09.449
if the electricity goes out.

13:09.480 --> 13:11.380
And then go out
into the shed

13:11.420 --> 13:13.809
and round up
batteries and lanterns.

13:13.860 --> 13:15.259
They should be
over the dryer.

13:15.290 --> 13:17.554
( thunder rumbles )

13:21.060 --> 13:22.357
Are you okay?

13:22.400 --> 13:25.528
I will be as soon as
Nova answers her phone.

13:25.570 --> 13:29.290
She's dodging calls like
I'm a damn bill collector.

13:29.340 --> 13:32.161
Nova,
an hour done passed
and gone,

13:32.210 --> 13:33.575
and you're still
not here.

13:33.610 --> 13:36.875
Get here before this storm
blows you away!

13:36.910 --> 13:38.468
( phone beeps off)

13:40.220 --> 13:41.812
( drill whirring )

13:48.290 --> 13:49.484
What do you think
you're doing?

13:49.520 --> 13:51.624
Saving you from getting
some new windows.

13:51.660 --> 13:54.299
This thing up here
all crooked and whatnot.

13:54.330 --> 13:56.548
You should be concerned
with boarding up windows

13:56.600 --> 13:58.898
where you live.

13:58.930 --> 14:00.568
That ain't here.

14:02.570 --> 14:04.208
(drill whirs)

14:07.110 --> 14:08.202
All right.

14:08.240 --> 14:09.468
Violet:
Is that my Blue?

14:09.510 --> 14:10.841
Blue:
Yup!

14:15.220 --> 14:17.939
Darla: _
How are you d0ing,
Miss Violet?

14:19.320 --> 14:21.880
Mom surprised me, Aunt Vi.

14:21.920 --> 14:24.081
You and me both, baby.

14:24.130 --> 14:25.483
Mwah!

14:29.560 --> 14:31.198
- You want to show me your room?
- Yeah!

14:31.230 --> 14:32.424
Come on, come on!

14:40.940 --> 14:45.400
Tell me, what the hell
is that girl doing here?

14:45.450 --> 14:47.918
She just showed up.
I ain't ask her.

14:47.950 --> 14:51.215
But Blue got all happy
about her being here.

14:51.250 --> 14:53.059
What you want me to do?

14:53.090 --> 14:56.514
Bad enough that Hollywood
done made his way
into my house,

14:56.560 --> 14:57.925
but Darla?

14:57.960 --> 15:00.326
Oh, unh-uh.
She got to go.

15:00.360 --> 15:02.351
What, you want me
to kick her out?

15:02.400 --> 15:04.618
Damn right, that's exactly
what I want you to do.

15:04.670 --> 15:06.467
In front of Blue?

15:06.500 --> 15:09.139
You ain't even thinking
how this is going to
mess with his head.

15:09.170 --> 15:12.606
That girl being here
is already messing
with his head.

15:12.640 --> 15:15.575
She treat being a mama
like a damn revolving door.

15:15.610 --> 15:17.475
So you right.
I ain't got no problem

15:17.510 --> 15:20.047
with revolving her ass
right on out of here.

15:24.720 --> 15:26.142
Holy...

15:26.190 --> 15:28.158
( rain patters,
thunder rumbles )

15:28.190 --> 15:30.158
( both sigh )

15:30.190 --> 15:32.920
( laughs )

15:39.730 --> 15:42.039
Hollywood:
