the house rules.

21:48.900 --> 21:51.801
"'That dog is crazy,‘
Emily said.

21:51.840 --> 21:55.378
'Crazy happy,‘ I answered.
'Just like me."'

21:55.410 --> 21:56.934
The end.

21:56.980 --> 21:58.538
Read another
story, please.

21:58.580 --> 22:00.673
I'm all out of books, baby.

22:00.720 --> 22:02.540
Ask Pop for another one.

22:02.580 --> 22:06.687
I can tell you one
I heard a long time ago.

22:06.720 --> 22:08.017
- Want to hear it?
- Yup.

22:08.060 --> 22:10.927
Okay, so there were
two best friends

22:10.960 --> 22:12.780
who used to play together.

22:12.830 --> 22:15.355
A girl named Olivia
and a boy named Oscar.

22:15.400 --> 22:17.868
Olivia never had toys,

22:17.900 --> 22:20.368
but Oscar would always
make sure that both of them

22:20.400 --> 22:22.459
had something to play with.

22:22.500 --> 22:24.001
Why didn't Olivia
have toys?

22:24.040 --> 22:27.100
Olivia's parents didn't
have a lot of money.

22:27.140 --> 22:28.801
Like me and Pop?

22:28.840 --> 22:32.549
No. You got a great daddy.

22:32.580 --> 22:34.878
Olivia didn't
have one like yours.

22:34.920 --> 22:37.946
Her pop wasn't around
to give her gifts like that.

22:37.990 --> 22:41.915
So, one day,
Oscar and Olivia were
playing in the woods,

22:41.960 --> 22:44.952
and came across
this beautiful toy.

22:44.990 --> 22:48.118
It would giggle,
play, tell jokes.

22:48.160 --> 22:50.867
They'd never seen
anything like it before,

22:50.900 --> 22:54.836
because it was a special toy,
magically made just for them.

22:54.870 --> 22:59.034
Oscar and Olivia
both fell in love with it.

22:59.070 --> 23:00.731
At first sight.

23:00.780 --> 23:03.704
They played together
with the toy every day.

23:03.750 --> 23:06.173
But then Oscar had to go
on a long vacation,

23:06.210 --> 23:08.075
leaving Olivia all alone.

23:08.120 --> 23:10.145
She'd write to Oscar
every day, telling him
all about

23:10.180 --> 23:12.717
her adventures with
their favorite toy,

23:12.750 --> 23:15.617
but she didn't know
when he'd return.

23:15.660 --> 23:17.924
She so was sad.

23:20.660 --> 23:23.959
One day,
Olivia made other friends.

23:24.000 --> 23:25.865
But they weren't
nice friends.

23:25.900 --> 23:27.162
Were they mean to her?

23:27.200 --> 23:32.069
Yeah, but Olivia
was really mean to herself,

23:32.110 --> 23:36.399
and she didn't take care
of her and Oscar's
magical toy...

23:38.510 --> 23:40.842
which made Oscar very angry.

23:40.880 --> 23:43.041
And when he finally
came back from vacation,

23:43.080 --> 23:46.083
he had to take the magical toy
away from Olivia,

23:46.120 --> 23:50.955
because he could give the toy
all the love Olivia wasn't.

23:50.990 --> 23:53.652
See, he loved and missed
the toy too.

23:53.700 --> 23:56.123
So, Oscar thought
the toy was his,

23:56.160 --> 23:58.993
and Olivia thought
the toy was hers.

23:59.030 --> 24:02.067
But they forgot that
they were best friends.

24:02.100 --> 24:03.806
They thought that they were
on different teams,

24:03.840 --> 24:05.808
when they really were always
on the same side.

24:12.250 --> 24:13.740
Yeah.

24:13.780 --> 24:16.544
It took a while,
but they did.

24:25.090 --> 24:26.580
( giggles )

24:29.200 --> 24:31.464
( rain pattering )

24:40.010 --> 24:41.602
( Hollywood grumbling )

24:41.640 --> 24:42.709
Nova:
Uh-uh, uh-uh.

24:42.740 --> 24:44.799
You reneging, Hollywood.

24:44.850 --> 24:45.976
The hell you say?

24:46.010 --> 24:47.238
You drop a club
when spades hit.

24:47.280 --> 24:50.147
You think I reneged,
point the book out.

24:50.180 --> 24:52.239
Why don't you use your
little stone to find it.

24:52.290 --> 24:55.509
You a liar, and the truth
ain't in you.

24:55.560 --> 24:57.858
( all laugh )

25:00.090 --> 25:02.126
You can't say it like Daddy,
Nova, so don't even try.

25:02.160 --> 25:03.252
Sorry, Daddy.

25:03.300 --> 25:05.598
That cigar hanging out
the side his mouth--

25:05.630 --> 25:07.791
You're dropping ashes
everywhere. About to burn
the house down.

25:07.840 --> 25:09.728
Violet:
That's when you knew
you were in trouble.

25:09.770 --> 25:11.533
Then he'd slap that card
on his forehead

25:11.570 --> 25:13.106
just waiting to set you.

25:13.140 --> 25:16.132
He would slam that card
down on the table and holler--

25:16.180 --> 25:16.874
All:
Bam!

25:16.910 --> 25:18.798
Wasn't no winning after that.

25:18.850 --> 25:19.942
( all laugh )

25:19.980 --> 25:22.676
Oh, that man could play,
I tell you.

25:27.720 --> 25:29.256
Micah, what's the score?

25:29.290 --> 25:32.157
Uh, 762...

25:32.190 --> 25:34.055
- ...to 690.
- We was only going to 500.

25:34.100 --> 25:36.625
We could have done won.

25:36.660 --> 25:38.321
How are you gonna play me
and your mama like that?

25:38.370 --> 25:40.224
Charley:
Remy, you were supposed
to be watching him.

25:40.270 --> 25:41.931
Listen, listen, listen,
when you come and stay
with me,

25:41.970 --> 25:43.289
I'm going to teach you.

25:43.340 --> 25:45.137
I'll tell you all
the little secrets, too.

25:45.170 --> 25:46.967
Micah hasn't been
accepted yet, so...

25:47.010 --> 25:48.898
He's a shoe-in.
Just watch.

25:48.940 --> 25:50.771
Yeah, he might be.

25:50.810 --> 25:52.107
What? You don't think
I can get in?

25:52.150 --> 25:55.210
No, baby, your application
is impeccable.

25:55.250 --> 25:57.138
They would be stupid
not to have you.

25:58.650 --> 26:00.311
They'd be downright dumb!

26:00.350 --> 26:02.557
( all laugh )

26:04.290 --> 26:06.622
You know, it's just that
Nova's not up to keeping Micah

26:06.660 --> 26:07.957
five days a week anyway.

26:08.000 --> 26:09.319
I know what I can handle,
Charley.

26:09.360 --> 26:10.292
Micah's no problem.

26:10.330 --> 26:13.299
Well, he's not ready
to stay with you yet.

26:13.330 --> 26:14.661
And why is that?

26:15.970 --> 26:17.062
( sighs )

26:17.100 --> 26:18.931
Your lifestyle, it's--

26:18.970 --> 26:21.109
It's not ideal
for someone like Micah.

26:21.140 --> 26:23.335
Lifestyle?
What is that even
supposed to mean?

26:24.910 --> 26:27.344
Nothing.
Want to play my hand?

26:32.920 --> 26:34.751
Nova:
You know what?

26:34.790 --> 26:37.350
You ain't said nothing
but bullshit

26:37.390 --> 26:38.857
up until now.

26:38.890 --> 26:40.221
So, what do you mean?

26:40.260 --> 26:42.649
Violet:
Y'all are going
to wake up Blue.

26:42.700 --> 26:45.726
If there's something
I want to say, Nova,
I'm going to say it.

26:45.770 --> 26:47.123
No, let her talk, Aunt Vi.

26:47.170 --> 26:49.764
Charley's been having sugar
poured on top of shit

26:49.800 --> 26:50.835
all her life.

26:50.870 --> 26:52.360
My life?

26:52.410 --> 26:55.334
My life is anything
but sugarcoated.

26:55.380 --> 26:57.974
I lost my husband.

26:58.010 --> 26:59.898
I lost my life.
Micah lost his life.

26:59.950 --> 27:02.373
Mi_cah could build a new life
if you weren't so damn
overprotective.

27:02.420 --> 27:05.184
And if you think my lifestyle
of sleeping with a woman

27:05.220 --> 27:08.109
is going to corrupt Micah,
you just hateful.

27:08.160 --> 27:10.116
I couldn't care less
about you sleeping
with a woman.

27:10.160 --> 27:11.354
Well, if that ain't it,

27:11.390 --> 27:13.324
then what lifestyle
you talking about?

27:15.200 --> 27:18.226
You're not a mother.
You grow weed.

27:18.270 --> 27:22.297
And you smoked that weed
with me. Now what?

27:23.440 --> 27:25.260
( sighs )

27:25.310 --> 27:27.266
I'm waiting.

27:27.310 --> 27:30.074
If it's for an apology,
you're going to be waiting
a long time.

27:30.110 --> 27:31.805
I don't want
a damn apology!

27:31.850 --> 27:33.442
I want you to be a grown woman
and come the hell out with it!

27:33.480 --> 27:36.176
You live in the Lower Ninth!

27:36.220 --> 27:38.211
I'm not going to put my son
in a position to be killed,

27:38.250 --> 27:40.787
shot, or in need
of a $10,000 bailout.

27:40.820 --> 27:42.310
Oh, here we go.

27:42.360 --> 27:44.328
No, no. You wanted me
to go there, so I'm there.

27:44.360 --> 27:47.727
Your ego is so big
you can't even apologize

27:47.760 --> 27:49.022
without making excuses.

27:49.060 --> 27:50.425
You were wrong!
You took the money!

27:50.460 --> 27:53.190
But no, no, no,
you can't say it.

27:53.230 --> 27:55.198
Nova:
Why say sorry for
something that I did

27:55.240 --> 27:57.094
- that was right?
- Charley: Oh, my God!

27:57.140 --> 27:58.266
It was for a greater good.

27:58.310 --> 28:00.107
